{'hadithnumber': 1, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said regarding the sea,\\n"It\'s water is purifying and its dead (animals) are lawful (to eat)." \\n\\n'}
{'hadithnumber': 2, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Water is pure and nothing can make it impure”.\\n\\n'}
{'hadithnumber': 3, 'text': 'Narrated Abu Umama Al-Bahili:\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Water cannot be rendered impure by anything except something which changes its smell, taste and colour”. \\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 4, 'text': '“Water is pure unless any impure thing is added which changes its smell, taste and colour”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 6, 'text': 'Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said:\\n“If there is enough water to fill two pots (Qulla), it carries no impurity,” Another version has: “It does not become unclean”.\\n{Al-Arba’a reported it. Ibn Khuzaima, Ibn Hibban and Al-Hakim graded it Sahih (sound)].'}
{'hadithnumber': 7, 'text': 'Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said:\\n“None of you should take a bath in stagnant water when he is sexually impure”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 8, 'text': '“None of you should urinate in stagnant water that is not flowing, and then take bath in it”.\\nA version of Muslim has the words “from it (i.e. the water)”.\\nA version of Abu Da’ud has: “One should not take bath in it from sexual impurity”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 9, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade a women to bathe with the water left over by a man and that a man should not bathe with the water left over by a woman (but instead) they should both take scoopfuls of the water together. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 10, 'text': 'Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (rad):\\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) used to bath with the water left over by Maimuna (rad) .'}
{'hadithnumber': 11, 'text': 'And Ashab As-Sunan (compilers of the prophet’s sayings) reported that one of the wives of the Prophet (ﷺ) took bath from a vessel, then came the Prophet (ﷺ) and when he wanted to take bath from that (vessel), she said, “I was sexually impure”. He said, “Water does not become sexually impure”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 12, 'text': 'Narrated by Abu Huraira (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The cleansing of the utensil belonging to one of you, after it has been licked by a dog, is to wash it seven times, and using soil for cleaning at the first time.” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 13, 'text': '“he should spill the content”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 14, 'text': 'At-Tirmidhi’s version has “using soil at the first or last time”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 15, 'text': 'Narrated Abu Qatada (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said about the cat that, “It is not unclean, but is one of those who intermingle with you.” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 16, 'text': 'Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad): \\nA Bedouin came and urinated in one corner of the mosque and the people shouted at him, but Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) stopped them, and when he finished urinating, the Prophet (ﷺ) ordered for a bucket of water which was spilt over it .'}
{'hadithnumber': 17, 'text': 'Narrated Ibn \'Umar (rad): \\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "Two types of dead animals and two types of bloods have been made lawful for us, the two types of dead animals are locusts and fish (seafood), while the two types of bloods are the liver and the spleen".'}
{'hadithnumber': 18, 'text': 'Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When a fly falls in the drink of one of you, he should fully dip it and then throw it away because there is disease in one of its wings and cure in the other”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 19, 'text': '“It (the fly) protects itself with the diseased wing (by dipping it first in a drink).'}
{'hadithnumber': 20, 'text': 'Narrated Abu Waqid Al-Laithi (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whatever (portion) is cut off from an animal when it is alive is dead (meat). .'}
{'hadithnumber': 21, 'text': 'Narrated Hudhaifa bin Al-Yaman (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Do not drink in silver or gold utensils, and do not eat in plates of such metals, for such things are for them (the disbelievers) in this worldly life and for you in the Hereafter.”'}
{'hadithnumber': 22, 'text': 'Narrated Umm Salama (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “He who drinks in a silver utensil is only swallowing Hell-fire in his stomach”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 23, 'text': 'Narrated  (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "When the skin is tanned it becomes purified.” . Al-Arba’a have the words: "Any skin that is tanned ... "'}
{'hadithnumber': 24, 'text': 'Narrated  (rad):\\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The tanning of a dead animal’s skin purifies it”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 25, 'text': 'Narrated  (rad):\\nSome people dragging a (dead) goat passed by the Prophet (ﷺ). He told them, “Had you better taken its skin”. They said, “It is dead”. He said, “Water and the leaves of the Acacia tree will purify it”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 26, 'text': 'Narrated  (rad):\\nI said “O Allah’s Messenger! We are living in a land inhabited by the people of the Scriptures; can we take our meals in their utensils?” He said, “If you can get utensils other than theirs, do not eat in theirs, but if you cannot get other than theirs, wash them and eat in them” .'}
{'hadithnumber': 27, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) and his Companions performed Wudu (ablution) from a skin water container belonging to a polytheist woman . (It is an extract of a long Hadith).'}
{'hadithnumber': 28, 'text': 'Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):\\nWhen the cup of the Prophet (ﷺ) got broken, he fixed it with a silver wire at the crack .'}
{'hadithnumber': 29, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) was asked about making vinegar out of wine. He said, “No (it is prohibited)”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 30, 'text': 'On the day of Khaibair, Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) commanded Abu Talha to announce: “Allah and His Messenger have prohibited for you (eating of) the flesh of the donkeys, for it is unclean”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 31, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) delivered a Khutba (religious talk) to us at Mina while mounted on his camel and its saliva was pouring on my shoulders .'}
{'hadithnumber': 32, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to wash the semen and then go out for prayer in that (very) garment and I could still see the trace of the washing on it.'}
{'hadithnumber': 33, 'text': '“I used to scrape it (the semen) off the garment of Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) and then he offered prayer with it.'}
{'hadithnumber': 34, 'text': 'Verily! I (‘Aisha) used to scrape it (the semen) off his garment with my nails while it was dry.'}
{'hadithnumber': 35, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The urine of a baby girl should be washed off and the urine of baby boy should be sprinkled (with water)”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 36, 'text': 'The Prophet (Saw) said regarding menstruation blood that smears a garment, “She should scrape it, rub it with water, then wash it and then she may pray in it”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 37, 'text': 'Khaula said, “O Messenger of Allah, suppose the (trace of) the blood does not go?” He said, “(Washing it with) water will suffice you and its trace won’t harm you”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 38, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said “Had I not feared burdening my Ummah, I would have commanded them to use Siwak with every ablution.” [Reported by Malik, Ahmad and An-Nasai. Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound) and Al-Bukhari mentioned as a Mu’allaq (suspended – without its chain of narrators).'}
{'hadithnumber': 39, 'text': 'Uthman (rad) called for water to perform ablution. He washed palms of his hands three times, then rinsed his mouth and sniffed water in his nose and then blew it out. He then washed his face three times. Thereafter he washed his right hand up to his elbow three times, then the left one likewise, then he passed wet hands on his head. Then he washed his right foot up to the ankle three times, then the left one likewise. He then said, “I saw Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) performing ablution like this ablution of mine”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 40, 'text': 'He (the Prophet) wiped his head (with water) only once. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 41, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) wiped his head from the forehead to the back of his head and then back to the forehead with his (wet) hands. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 42, 'text': '"He started with the front of his head, moved them (his hands) to the nape of his neck, and then returned them to the place where he started."'}
{'hadithnumber': 43, 'text': '“Then he (Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ)) wiped his head, inserted his index finger in his ears and wiped the exterior of his ears with thumbs”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 44, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you wakes up from his sleep, he must blow of his nose three times, for the Satan spends the night inside one’s nostrils”  .'}
{'hadithnumber': 45, 'text': 'Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you wakes up from his sleep, he must not put his hand in a utensil till he washed it three times, for he does not know where his hand was (while he slept)”.\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 46, 'text': 'Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said: “Perform a perfect Wudu run (your fingers) through the fingers of the hands and the toes, and if not fasting, sniff water up well inside the nose”. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 47, 'text': '“If you perform ablution rinse your mouth”.'}
{'hadithnumber': 48, 'text': 'While performing Wudu, the Prophet (ﷺ) would run (his fingers) through his beard. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 49, 'text': 'Two thirds of a Mudd (of water) was brought to he Prophet (ﷺ) (for ablution) so he began rubbing his arms. .'}
{'hadithnumber': 50, 'text': 'He saw the Prophet (ﷺ) taking some water to wipe his ears other than the water he had taken to wipe his head. .'}
